summary: t.A.T.u. was a popular Russian music duo made up of Lena Katina and Julia Volkova. They started singing together as kids in a group called Neposedy. Their first album, "200 Po Vstrechnoy," was a big hit in Eastern Europe. This led to an English version, "200 km/h in the Wrong Lane," which became famous worldwide, especially with songs like "All the Things She Said." They even performed at the Eurovision Song Contest. After some changes, they released more albums and tried other projects. In 2011, they went their separate ways but sometimes reunited for special performances.
title: T.A.T.u.
